This paper is primarily focused on exploring the connection between Binary Neural Networks and Spiking Neural Networks, which are both subfields of Neural Networks and fall under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. The paper also deals with large-scale image datasets like CIFAR-100 and ImageNet, which are commonly used in computer vision research, indicating a possible connection to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also discusses algorithmic techniques for reducing compute requirements, which is a common theme in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper explores design-time and run-time optimization techniques, which are relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of hardware accelerators, which is relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
